enumGroup.groupDescription: Reasons why an infusion pump mechanism is stopped.

enum.description: Pump has been stopped as a result of an alarm condition.
Status when an infusion is complete and not followed by a KVO.
Pump has been stopped by the clinician for a short time after which an alert may signal.
Pump has been programmed with either a future start time or a delay period after which the infusion will begin.
Pump has been powered on or selected and possibly programmed but not "started".
Pump has been programmed and started but is in patient-dose mode or multi-dosing mode and not currently delivering fluid.
Pump has been programmed and "paused" for an indeterminate period (possibly with configured max period limit).
The pump is transitioning to a new infusing mode (e.g., piggyback to primary switchover). Used when pump-stopped-delivery-complete is not appropriate.
